Installation and Setup

Clone the repository:

git clone <repo-url>
cd <project-folder>


Create and activate a virtual environment:

python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate  # macOS/Linux


Install dependencies:

pip install flask numpy pillow scikit-learn


Run the application:

python app.py


Open your browser and go to:

http://127.0.0.1:5000

How It Works

The user uploads an image through the browser

JavaScript displays an image preview immediately

Flask receives the image on form submission

The image is resized and converted into a NumPy array

K-Means clustering is used to find the 10 dominant colors

The results are rendered as color cards on the page